René Navarre https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ren%C3%A9_Navarre 0 René Navarre (8 July 1877 – 8 February 1968) was a French actor of the silent era. He appeared in 109 films between 1910 and 1946. He was born in Limoges, Haute-Vienne and died in Azay-sur-Cher, Indre-et-Loire. He was often credited as the mononym Navarre. His most famous role was probably the master criminal Fantômas.
